1
00:00:00,383 --> 00:00:04,466
(suspenseful introductory music)

2
00:01:00,420 --> 00:01:02,280
Multiple personality,

3
00:01:02,280 --> 00:01:03,850
I don't feel right calling it that,

4
00:01:03,850 --> 00:01:05,293
That's like I'm possessed.

5
00:01:06,730 --> 00:01:08,083
Dissociative disorder.

6
00:01:09,030 --> 00:01:10,440
That's better, yeah.

7
00:01:10,440 --> 00:01:11,980
That's much better.

8
00:01:11,980 --> 00:01:16,240
Like I can't make connections with my selves

9
00:01:16,240 --> 00:01:17,433
or with the world.

10
00:01:18,380 --> 00:01:21,500
It's like, sometimes I'll open a door somewhere,

11
00:01:21,500 --> 00:01:24,593
and I'll be in a whole different place altogether.

12
00:01:25,950 --> 00:01:27,320
And it'll be two hours later,

13
00:01:27,320 --> 00:01:29,723
or even a whole day or night.

14
00:01:33,039 --> 00:01:35,101
I just lose track of time in between.

15
00:01:35,101 --> 00:01:37,700
(suspenseful music begins)

16
00:01:37,700 --> 00:01:39,053
Like when I met Sean,

17
00:01:40,080 --> 00:01:41,530
I don't really remember that,

18
00:01:42,570 --> 00:01:44,020
or the wedding.

19
00:01:44,020 --> 00:01:49,003
Though everybody tells me I was never happier.

20
00:01:49,890 --> 00:01:52,163
I do remember Molly being born.

21
00:01:53,352 --> 00:01:54,185
Oh God.

22
00:01:56,120 --> 00:01:58,423
That's when I learned what love really meant.

23
00:02:04,290 --> 00:02:08,842
And when Rosie came along, feeling just doubled.

24
00:02:10,750 --> 00:02:12,590
Having my family made me believe

25
00:02:13,570 --> 00:02:16,320
that everything was gonna turn out wonderful after all.

26
00:02:18,340 --> 00:02:22,030
Then my father was in his office last August

27
00:02:24,720 --> 00:02:25,553
and everything came unglued.

28
00:02:25,553 --> 00:02:30,553
Jim. Jim?

29
00:02:30,880 --> 00:02:33,463
(Jim groaning)

30
00:02:34,367 --> 00:02:35,950
Jim?

31
00:02:35,950 --> 00:02:36,783
Hello, Jim?

32
00:02:37,970 --> 00:02:38,803
Jim?

33
00:02:42,803 --> 00:02:46,803
(suspenseful music intensifies)

34
00:02:55,224 --> 00:02:56,574
Dr. Tremayne?

35
00:02:56,574 --> 00:02:58,418
(telephone ringing)

36
00:02:58,418 --> 00:03:00,086
Oh my God.

37
00:03:03,747 --> 00:03:06,747
(telephone ringing)

38
00:03:14,400 --> 00:03:15,233
Hello.

39
00:03:17,060 --> 00:03:17,893
Oh, my God.

40
00:03:19,320 --> 00:03:20,153
Suzy.

41
00:03:21,567 --> 00:03:22,400
Suzy!

42
00:03:23,788 --> 00:03:27,538
(hurried footsteps thumping)

43
00:03:30,597 --> 00:03:32,190
Mom.

44
00:03:32,190 --> 00:03:33,380
He's asked for you.

45
00:03:36,404 --> 00:03:37,237
Daddy,

46
00:03:38,473 --> 00:03:39,305
Daddy.

47
00:03:40,523 --> 00:03:41,606
Hi, hi, hi.

48
00:03:42,739 --> 00:03:44,481
Hi, Daddy.

49
00:03:44,481 --> 00:03:47,727
(monitor beeping)
Jim? Jimmy?

50
00:03:47,727 --> 00:03:48,622
Code blue!

51
00:03:48,622 --> 00:03:50,143
(nurses and doctors frantically speaking)

52
00:03:50,143 --> 00:03:52,163
Code blue, I need an EpiPen.

53
00:03:52,163 --> 00:03:52,996
Coming through.

54
00:03:52,996 --> 00:03:56,572
I need the paddles please, give me a charge.

55
00:03:56,572 --> 00:03:57,530
Get in here with the paddles

56
00:03:57,530 --> 00:03:59,447
Oh, my God, somebody!

57
00:04:01,238 --> 00:04:02,821
(heart monitor goes flat)
Clear!

58
00:04:02,821 --> 00:04:04,333
One more time, go in again.

59
00:04:05,279 --> 00:04:07,457
Clear!
Oh my God. Oh my God!

60
00:04:07,457 --> 00:04:09,499
Give me a charge again, one more time.

61
00:04:09,499 --> 00:04:11,416
Daddy!
Clear!

62
00:04:12,307 --> 00:04:14,123
Bonnie, look what I did.

63
00:04:18,240 --> 00:04:19,072
Good honey.

64
00:04:20,860 --> 00:04:22,967
Is it okay maybe if I play too?

65
00:04:24,220 --> 00:04:25,803
If you want to that'd be fun.

66
00:04:27,628 --> 00:04:31,128
(tense suspenseful music)

67
00:04:35,486 --> 00:04:37,456
Look what mommy's doing.

68
00:04:37,456 --> 00:04:38,956
I wanna do that.

69
00:04:41,345 --> 00:04:44,095
(girls giggling)

70
00:04:46,661 --> 00:04:48,425
So what's going on?

71
00:04:48,425 --> 00:04:49,640
We're coloring, Daddy.

72
00:04:49,640 --> 00:04:51,030
Yeah.

73
00:04:51,030 --> 00:04:52,020
Girls, why don't you go inside,

74
00:04:52,020 --> 00:04:53,159
and clean your face and your hands.

75
00:04:53,159 --> 00:04:54,550
Come on, let's go.

76
00:04:54,550 --> 00:04:56,063
Lookie my pretty picture.

77
00:04:57,650 --> 00:04:59,270
What are you doing?

78
00:04:59,270 --> 00:05:00,103
Why aren't you dressed?

79
00:05:00,103 --> 00:05:01,710
We have to be there in 15 minutes.

80
00:05:03,150 --> 00:05:04,150
Where?

81
00:05:04,150 --> 00:05:05,200
The funeral.

82
00:05:08,400 --> 00:05:12,352
Uh, I can't go like this.

83
00:05:12,352 --> 00:05:13,435
No kidding.

84
00:05:15,191 --> 00:05:16,543
You take the girls.

85
00:05:18,070 --> 00:05:20,343
I'll get dressed and I'll meet you there, okay?

86
00:05:25,727 --> 00:05:28,810
(door bell jingling)

87
00:05:29,970 --> 00:05:31,393
Hi, can I help you?

88
00:05:38,940 --> 00:05:40,232
Do you see this dress?

89
00:05:40,232 --> 00:05:41,914
This is a really nice one.

90
00:05:41,914 --> 00:05:43,313
And so it is said,

91
00:05:43,313 --> 00:05:46,320
that I say Dr. Tremayne was far more

92
00:05:46,320 --> 00:05:48,220
than just a caring citizen,

93
00:05:48,220 --> 00:05:50,233
and a loving husband and father.

94
00:05:51,150 --> 00:05:53,480
He was more even, then one of those rare- (fades out).

95
00:05:53,480 --> 00:05:54,980
Another scotch, hun.

96
00:05:58,260 --> 00:05:59,093
Ginger.

97
00:06:02,000 --> 00:06:02,833
It's Huff.

98
00:06:06,214 --> 00:06:07,047
Sup?

99
00:06:08,630 --> 00:06:10,160
Heard you were living with some guy.

100
00:06:10,160 --> 00:06:11,993
Oh yeah, on and off.

101
00:06:13,285 --> 00:06:15,285
Wanna make some money?

102
00:06:16,346 --> 00:06:17,179
Eddie,

103
00:06:20,933 --> 00:06:22,223
looking for a game?

104
00:06:23,430 --> 00:06:24,263
Sure, why not.

105
00:06:26,088 --> 00:06:28,185
Eddie, this is Ginger.

106
00:06:28,185 --> 00:06:29,580
Hey Ginger.

107
00:06:29,580 --> 00:06:31,016
How ya doing?

108
00:06:31,016 --> 00:06:32,849
I'm doing just fine.

109
00:06:36,620 --> 00:06:39,918
(slow sensual music)

110
00:06:39,918 --> 00:06:40,868
You owe me 20 more.

111
00:06:48,530 --> 00:06:52,113
(Eddie and Ginger moaning)

112
00:06:54,382 --> 00:06:59,382
You like that? You like that?

113
00:06:59,481 --> 00:07:00,314
Come on.

114
00:07:07,803 --> 00:07:09,550
No, no.
What happened?

115
00:07:09,550 --> 00:07:10,913
Everybody's freaking out.

116
00:07:12,300 --> 00:07:13,133
You missed the funeral.

117
00:07:13,133 --> 00:07:15,120
I called and called, why didn't you answer?

118
00:07:15,120 --> 00:07:16,210
Who are you?

119
00:07:16,210 --> 00:07:17,043
Suzy cut it out.

120
00:07:17,043 --> 00:07:18,163
Come on, wake up.

121
00:07:19,260 --> 00:07:20,861
We gotta call your mom, she's frantic.

122
00:07:20,861 --> 00:07:22,332
Mom? Mommy!

123
00:07:22,332 --> 00:07:23,166
Shh!

124
00:07:23,166 --> 00:07:25,775
We waited a half hour for you before we started the funeral.

125
00:07:25,775 --> 00:07:27,318
My head hurts!

126
00:07:27,318 --> 00:07:28,800
(Sean sighs)

127
00:07:28,800 --> 00:07:30,000
You want some aspirin?

128
00:07:31,618 --> 00:07:32,868
I can't swallow.

129
00:07:34,650 --> 00:07:37,214
Do you want those baby aspirin again?

130
00:07:37,214 --> 00:07:38,047
Stay!

131
00:07:38,891 --> 00:07:40,462
Stay.

132
00:07:40,462 --> 00:07:41,295
Shh,

133
00:07:42,150 --> 00:07:43,643
take it easy.

134
00:07:43,643 --> 00:07:45,274
It's okay.

135
00:07:45,274 --> 00:07:46,691
Don't leave me.

136
00:07:47,644 --> 00:07:48,811
Dad, my daddy.

137
00:07:50,748 --> 00:07:53,520
(Suzy crying)

138
00:07:53,520 --> 00:07:54,370
I know, I know.

139
00:07:55,370 --> 00:07:56,203
It's awful.

140
00:07:57,400 --> 00:07:58,950
I remember when my father died.

141
00:08:01,630 --> 00:08:02,593
I was crazy too.

142
00:08:05,480 --> 00:08:06,313
Sean.

143
00:08:08,083 --> 00:08:09,166
I missed him.

144
00:08:31,125 --> 00:08:31,957
Oh my god.

145
00:08:32,818 --> 00:08:36,152
(dramatic music begins)

146
00:08:54,403 --> 00:08:57,068
I'm sorry Daddy, I wasn't here.

147
00:08:57,068 --> 00:08:59,648
I'm sorry I missed your funeral.

148
00:08:59,648 --> 00:09:01,480
I'll be a good girl, I will.

149
00:09:01,480 --> 00:09:03,547
The door opened, and his father peered in.

150
00:09:03,547 --> 00:09:05,127
"You're already dressed," he said.

151
00:09:05,127 --> 00:09:05,960
"Yes," said Bertick.

152
00:09:05,960 --> 00:09:07,970
Mom, Dad's skipping again!

153
00:09:07,970 --> 00:09:09,187
No I'm not!

154
00:09:09,187 --> 00:09:11,962
"Yes," said Bertick, that's not skipping.

155
00:09:11,962 --> 00:09:12,833
Yes you are, right there.

156
00:09:12,833 --> 00:09:14,464
(Sean chuckles)

157
00:09:14,464 --> 00:09:17,304
Mom, can you read to us?

158
00:09:17,304 --> 00:09:18,827
Sure. Hello.

159
00:09:18,827 --> 00:09:19,660
Thanks, Dad.

160
00:09:19,660 --> 00:09:21,135
You're impossible.

161
00:09:21,135 --> 00:09:22,135
Right there.

162
00:09:23,530 --> 00:09:24,363
Okay.

163
00:09:24,363 --> 00:09:27,379
"Stick out your tongue," said his father.

164
00:09:27,379 --> 00:09:30,134
"more, more, more! Say Ah."

165
00:09:30,134 --> 00:09:32,112
Ahhh.

166
00:09:32,112 --> 00:09:35,480
"Your throat is clear, your nose is stuffed.

167
00:09:35,480 --> 00:09:38,090
I'll make some broth," said Bertick's mother.

168
00:09:38,090 --> 00:09:39,007
Ewwww.

169
00:09:39,007 --> 00:09:41,710
Ew? Have you girls brushed your teeth?

170
00:09:41,710 --> 00:09:42,543
I have!

171
00:09:42,543 --> 00:09:43,775
No you haven't
I have.

172
00:09:43,775 --> 00:09:44,608
Yes I have.
Get in there,

173
00:09:44,608 --> 00:09:45,940
I'll finished the story after.
Mommy, I have too!

174
00:09:45,940 --> 00:09:47,904
No you haven't, you get in there.

175
00:09:47,904 --> 00:09:49,775
That big monster's gonna get you if you don't go.

176
00:09:49,775 --> 00:09:51,141
(girls squealing)

177
00:09:51,141 --> 00:09:52,770
Brush your teeth, brush your teeth.

178
00:09:52,770 --> 00:09:53,603
Good girls.

179
00:09:53,603 --> 00:09:54,436
Suzy?

180
00:09:56,820 --> 00:09:58,990
Where'd this money come from?

181
00:09:58,990 --> 00:10:01,090
My sock drawer.

182
00:10:01,090 --> 00:10:02,960
Well it was on the floor.

183
00:10:02,960 --> 00:10:05,810
Well, it must have slipped out.

184
00:10:05,810 --> 00:10:06,910
I'm waitressing again.

185
00:10:07,830 --> 00:10:09,320
Where?

186
00:10:09,320 --> 00:10:10,603
It's only part- time.

187
00:10:13,760 --> 00:10:16,240
Well who's taking care of the girls?

188
00:10:16,240 --> 00:10:18,010
My mom, mostly.

189
00:10:18,010 --> 00:10:19,340
Are you okay with that?

190
00:10:19,340 --> 00:10:21,550
I have to be, 'til we get ahead.

191
00:10:21,550 --> 00:10:23,719
Then maybe I can take some classes.

192
00:10:23,719 --> 00:10:24,552
(phone ringing)
Classes?

193
00:10:24,552 --> 00:10:26,610
What are you talking about?

194
00:10:26,610 --> 00:10:28,200
Hello.

195
00:10:28,200 --> 00:10:31,243
Ginger. Got you another date.

196
00:10:33,690 --> 00:10:35,740
I'm sorry, what number are you calling?

197
00:10:37,540 --> 00:10:38,373
Oh, I get it.

198
00:10:38,373 --> 00:10:40,480
I get it, that guy's there huh?

199
00:10:40,480 --> 00:10:42,630
Listen, call me back on my car phone, okay?

200
00:10:45,120 --> 00:10:46,190
You must have the wrong number,

201
00:10:46,190 --> 00:10:47,840
there's no one here by that name.

202
00:10:50,922 --> 00:10:53,172
What kind of classes are you talking about?

203
00:10:55,690 --> 00:10:56,523
For teaching.

204
00:10:58,000 --> 00:10:59,083
I wanna be a teacher.

205
00:11:00,140 --> 00:11:01,420
For what?

206
00:11:01,420 --> 00:11:02,633
You always hated school.

207
00:11:04,500 --> 00:11:05,693
I want to work, okay?

208
00:11:07,010 --> 00:11:08,032
We've got bills to pay,

209
00:11:08,032 --> 00:11:09,980
and I don't want to have to ask my mom for money.

210
00:11:09,980 --> 00:11:11,830
She's got problems of her own anyway.

211
00:11:13,430 --> 00:11:16,250
Look, I'm sorry I'm not a doctor like your father was,

212
00:11:16,250 --> 00:11:17,660
but at least give me enough respect

213
00:11:17,660 --> 00:11:19,823
that if you get a job, to tell me about it.

214
00:11:21,690 --> 00:11:23,490
Sean, where are you going?

215
00:11:23,490 --> 00:11:24,790
To put the girls to bed.

216
00:11:28,894 --> 00:11:32,811
(girls squealing and laughing)

217
00:11:42,117 --> 00:11:43,614
Mommy, mommy, mommy, mommy.

218
00:11:43,614 --> 00:11:45,467
Mommy, come out and do the new one.

219
00:11:45,467 --> 00:11:48,445
Hold your horses.
Aww. Mom, please.

220
00:11:48,445 --> 00:11:49,278
Come out.

221
00:11:53,709 --> 00:11:55,333
Ready?

222
00:11:58,800 --> 00:12:02,753
Down by the river where the green grass grows.

223
00:12:02,753 --> 00:12:07,753
One, two, three, four, five.
(girls giggling)

224
00:12:10,878 --> 00:12:13,545
(ominous music)

225
00:12:15,212 --> 00:12:16,045
Come on.

226
00:12:20,620 --> 00:12:22,780
It seems you've inherited

227
00:12:22,780 --> 00:12:24,990
some of my brother's lawsuits.

228
00:12:24,990 --> 00:12:26,260
Malpractice suits.

229
00:12:26,260 --> 00:12:28,050
Yes, I just found out about it,

230
00:12:28,050 --> 00:12:31,470
It's nothing to worry about, it happens all the time.

231
00:12:31,470 --> 00:12:33,630
I'm going to tell your mother on Thursday.

232
00:12:33,630 --> 00:12:35,240
Oh, it doesn't matter what you tell Martha,

233
00:12:35,240 --> 00:12:37,093
she only believes what she wants to.

234
00:12:39,207 --> 00:12:40,040
Well, if you need money,

235
00:12:40,040 --> 00:12:41,350
I'm sure she'd give you a loan.

236
00:12:42,310 --> 00:12:43,143
Loan?

237
00:12:44,750 --> 00:12:45,750
I earned that money.

238
00:12:48,360 --> 00:12:49,553
In what sense, Suzy?

239
00:12:55,870 --> 00:12:57,020
I was counting on it.

240
00:12:58,690 --> 00:12:59,690
That's what I meant.

241
00:13:05,581 --> 00:13:08,414
(cars screeching)

242
00:13:28,995 --> 00:13:33,578
(echoing of cars and tires screeching)

243
00:13:46,753 --> 00:13:50,003
(ominous music begins)

244
00:13:51,313 --> 00:13:52,665
Car?

245
00:13:52,665 --> 00:13:53,498
Mommy?

246
00:13:54,498 --> 00:13:59,329
Daddy?
(car alarm beeping)

247
00:13:59,329 --> 00:14:00,300
Where's the car?

248
00:14:00,300 --> 00:14:02,050
Where'd I put my car?

249
00:14:03,018 --> 00:14:03,851
Car?

250
00:14:08,275 --> 00:14:09,358
Bad car, bad.

251
00:14:10,869 --> 00:14:14,014
Bad, where were you hiding, car?

252
00:14:14,014 --> 00:14:15,514
Bad, bad, bad car.

253
00:14:17,570 --> 00:14:18,653
Bad. Bad car.

254
00:14:20,790 --> 00:14:21,623
Bad.

255
00:14:23,327 --> 00:14:24,660
Suzy?

256
00:14:26,798 --> 00:14:28,400
What?

257
00:14:28,400 --> 00:14:31,250
You were talking about McWhorter College.

258
00:14:31,250 --> 00:14:32,083
What about it?

259
00:14:33,430 --> 00:14:35,640
You said you wanted to go there.

260
00:14:35,640 --> 00:14:37,980
It's only $300 a credit.

261
00:14:37,980 --> 00:14:39,080
What about the SATs?

262
00:14:40,410 --> 00:14:42,333
Don't they require around 1,200?

263
00:14:43,420 --> 00:14:45,870
Girls, please be careful over there.

264
00:14:45,870 --> 00:14:46,760
I'll get it,

265
00:14:46,760 --> 00:14:47,633
I'll get 1,200.

266
00:14:48,820 --> 00:14:51,963
Maybe you shouldn't set your sights quite so high.

267
00:14:53,040 --> 00:14:55,323
Remember all the trouble you were having in school?

268
00:14:56,860 --> 00:14:58,263
You really don't remember?

269
00:14:59,720 --> 00:15:01,410
Maybe that's why you don't test well.

270
00:15:01,410 --> 00:15:03,230
Which is only one kind of intelligence,

271
00:15:03,230 --> 00:15:06,270
but unfortunately is what school's all about.

272
00:15:06,270 --> 00:15:07,680
Mom, I want to be a teacher.

273
00:15:07,680 --> 00:15:10,880
I wanna help people, I wanna make things clear.

274
00:15:10,880 --> 00:15:11,713
I understand.

275
00:15:13,710 --> 00:15:16,050
Just because you didn't work.

276
00:15:16,050 --> 00:15:17,600
What are you talking about?

277
00:15:17,600 --> 00:15:20,173
I managed a restaurant from the time you were 11.

278
00:15:21,060 --> 00:15:24,443
I swear, sometimes your brain is like Swiss cheese.

279
00:15:25,520 --> 00:15:26,353
Here.

280
00:15:28,100 --> 00:15:31,403
Oh, I can't take any more of your money, Mom.

281
00:15:33,530 --> 00:15:34,980
You said you needed a loan.

282
00:15:37,990 --> 00:15:39,533
Just now, at lunch.

