00:44:52,930 --> 00:44:54,620
to begin to talk to each other,

849
00:44:54,620 --> 00:44:57,632
so that we can finally blend and become one.

850
00:44:57,632 --> 00:44:59,240
(Suzy sighs)

851
00:44:59,240 --> 00:45:01,463
You want us to ask our mother for money.

852
00:45:02,680 --> 00:45:06,380
I'm warning you, Ginger will never countenance that.

853
00:45:06,380 --> 00:45:07,230
Why not?

854
00:45:09,809 --> 00:45:11,209
Because that's her policy.

855
00:45:12,452 --> 00:45:15,483
Well could you explain that to me?

856
00:45:17,241 --> 00:45:19,010
Oh please, Eric.

857
00:45:19,010 --> 00:45:20,870
Don't be disingenuous.

858
00:45:20,870 --> 00:45:23,430
I'm sure you've read the same texts we have.

859
00:45:23,430 --> 00:45:26,440
Of all recorded cases of multiple personality,

860
00:45:26,440 --> 00:45:29,070
fewer than 5% have failed to demonstrate

861
00:45:29,070 --> 00:45:31,993
an etiology of repeated traumatic abuse.

862
00:45:33,100 --> 00:45:34,050
That's very good.

863
00:45:36,060 --> 00:45:38,210
Are you saying that your mother abused you?

864
00:45:40,220 --> 00:45:41,660
You're saying that.

865
00:45:41,660 --> 00:45:43,110
You don't remember, do you?

866
00:45:44,800 --> 00:45:46,770
Well what about Ginger?

867
00:45:46,770 --> 00:45:47,713
Does she remember?

868
00:45:52,836 --> 00:45:55,503
(Suzy chuckles)

869
00:45:57,884 --> 00:45:58,717
Well.

870
00:46:00,800 --> 00:46:03,030
Ginger won't talk to you.

871
00:46:03,030 --> 00:46:03,880
Why not?

872
00:46:06,283 --> 00:46:09,533
(Suzy speaking French)

873
00:46:10,579 --> 00:46:11,729
Well what about Bonnie?

874
00:46:12,620 --> 00:46:13,453
Bonnie?

875
00:46:14,380 --> 00:46:16,153
Do you wanna come out and play again?

876
00:46:17,310 --> 00:46:19,430
Of course, we could always forget to pay you,

877
00:46:19,430 --> 00:46:20,263
couldn't we?

878
00:46:21,890 --> 00:46:23,323
It's another alternative.

879
00:46:24,240 --> 00:46:25,073
Bonnie?

880
00:46:31,090 --> 00:46:31,923
Hi.

881
00:46:33,090 --> 00:46:34,113
It's me, Eric.

882
00:46:38,300 --> 00:46:39,500
Bonnie, what do you see?

883
00:46:44,450 --> 00:46:45,283
Who am I?

884
00:46:52,710 --> 00:46:53,543
Suzy.

885
00:46:55,730 --> 00:46:57,483
I need to talk to Suzy now.

886
00:47:00,260 --> 00:47:01,093
Suzy!

887
00:47:05,790 --> 00:47:07,040
Why are you doing this?

888
00:47:09,710 --> 00:47:11,580
Because sweetheart,

889
00:47:11,580 --> 00:47:13,690
between therapy and chauffeuring the kids,

890
00:47:13,690 --> 00:47:15,290
you can't be everywhere at once.

891
00:47:19,056 --> 00:47:19,956
Are you all right?

892
00:47:21,063 --> 00:47:21,896
Yeah.

893
00:47:23,380 --> 00:47:25,767
Listen, why don't you go lie down,

894
00:47:25,767 --> 00:47:28,767
and I'll make sure that Sean and the girls get their dinner.

895
00:47:32,110 --> 00:47:35,503
Incidentally, I sent a check to your therapist directly.

896
00:47:39,700 --> 00:47:41,550
Are you sure you're okay with that?

897
00:47:42,504 --> 00:47:43,504
Of course.

898
00:47:44,536 --> 00:47:47,710
It makes me feel useful now that your dad is gone.

899
00:47:50,960 --> 00:47:52,810
How's your therapy coming by the way?

900
00:47:54,180 --> 00:47:55,013
I don't know.

901
00:47:56,106 --> 00:47:57,790
I guess I'm finding out some stuff.

902
00:47:57,790 --> 00:48:00,263
Well, so long as it doesn't become a crutch.

903
00:48:01,840 --> 00:48:02,673
Thanks, Mom.

904
00:48:07,593 --> 00:48:08,710
(door slams)

905
00:48:08,710 --> 00:48:09,643
Lying bitch!

906
00:48:12,245 --> 00:48:16,657
(Suzy breathing heavily)
(ominous music)

907
00:48:16,657 --> 00:48:19,157
Think you can hide it from me?

908
00:48:25,565 --> 00:48:28,398
(cars rushing by)

909
00:48:29,437 --> 00:48:30,270
Hey!

910
00:48:34,791 --> 00:48:35,974
Come on!

911
00:48:35,974 --> 00:48:38,891
(glass shattering)

912
00:48:41,331 --> 00:48:44,164
(window thudding)

913
00:48:45,583 --> 00:48:46,416
Okay, Mom.

914
00:48:51,411 --> 00:48:52,244
Let's see.

915
00:48:59,408 --> 00:49:00,830
Where'd she put it.

916
00:49:00,830 --> 00:49:02,130
Where'd you hide it Mommy?

917
00:49:05,040 --> 00:49:06,943
Oh, Daddy's office?

918
00:49:08,601 --> 00:49:09,434
Clever.

919
00:49:15,655 --> 00:49:18,080
(Suzy gasps)

920
00:49:18,080 --> 00:49:19,959
Didn't even open these.

921
00:49:19,959 --> 00:49:22,709
(papers falling)

922
00:49:45,120 --> 00:49:46,823
Claimant, Natalie Adams.

923
00:49:49,907 --> 00:49:52,311
(loud thud)

924
00:49:52,311 --> 00:49:55,532
(dogs barking)

925
00:49:55,532 --> 00:49:58,282
(metal scraping)

926
00:49:59,309 --> 00:50:02,976
(ominous music intensifies)

927
00:50:05,423 --> 00:50:08,756
(dogs continue barking)

928
00:50:35,304 --> 00:50:37,721
(Suzy gasps)

929
00:50:52,432 --> 00:50:54,781
That'll teach you, Natalie Adams.

930
00:50:54,781 --> 00:50:56,293
(phone ringing)
Honey, get the phone.

931
00:51:09,060 --> 00:51:11,767
Ginger, I don't know about phone tag.

932
00:51:13,426 --> 00:51:15,203
I gotta get out of here.

933
00:51:15,203 --> 00:51:16,036
Good,

934
00:51:16,036 --> 00:51:18,610
'cause I need you to make another run to San Diego for me.

935
00:51:18,610 --> 00:51:20,523
Trevor again? How much?

936
00:51:21,670 --> 00:51:22,820
How much do you need?

937
00:51:24,232 --> 00:51:27,127
Hm. Enough for a ticket to Hawaii.

938
00:51:28,730 --> 00:51:30,763
I'm serious hun, I'm going nuts.

939
00:51:31,723 --> 00:51:34,513
Yeah, you never did strike me as much of a homebody.

940
00:51:37,390 --> 00:51:40,129
Does this mean I'm gonna lose my best girl?

941
00:51:40,129 --> 00:51:42,060
(Suzy chuckles)

942
00:51:42,060 --> 00:51:43,410
You're breaking my heart.

943
00:51:45,360 --> 00:51:48,050
You're not gonna flake out on me again, are you?

944
00:51:48,050 --> 00:51:49,820
No, no way.

945
00:51:49,820 --> 00:51:51,423
This has gotta work on Dad.

946
00:51:55,004 --> 00:51:56,453
See ya in an hour!

947
00:51:56,453 --> 00:51:58,570
Bye! I'll miss you!

948
00:51:58,570 --> 00:52:00,624
See you tonight!

949
00:52:00,624 --> 00:52:01,897
I love you, I'll miss you!

950
00:52:01,897 --> 00:52:05,730
Come on, come on, let's get inside.

951
00:52:06,830 --> 00:52:08,393
Hi there, can I help you?

952
00:52:09,820 --> 00:52:11,920
Yes please, can I see that there?

953
00:52:14,290 --> 00:52:15,333
That's a pretty gun.

954
00:52:16,730 --> 00:52:17,563
This one?

955
00:52:17,563 --> 00:52:19,671
Yeah, that one there.

956
00:52:19,671 --> 00:52:21,162
All right.

957
00:52:21,162 --> 00:52:22,745
Thank you mister.

958
00:52:36,620 --> 00:52:38,750
Let's go home.

959
00:52:38,750 --> 00:52:39,963
Let's stop this.

960
00:52:48,550 --> 00:52:49,883
Well, let's just see.

961
00:52:52,350 --> 00:52:55,983
(loud country music)

962
00:52:55,983 --> 00:52:59,233
(bar patrons chatting)

963
00:53:08,749 --> 00:53:09,848
How you doing, precious?

964
00:53:09,848 --> 00:53:11,015
How you doing.

965
00:53:12,205 --> 00:53:13,342
Wanna get something to eat?

966
00:53:13,342 --> 00:53:14,175
Oh sure.

967
00:53:17,323 --> 00:53:18,789
(Suzy laughs)

968
00:53:18,789 --> 00:53:20,660
Hey, baby, how about a dance.

969
00:53:20,660 --> 00:53:22,129
How 'bout a sandwich.

970
00:53:22,129 --> 00:53:24,379
How about a little later.

971
00:53:27,690 --> 00:53:29,250
Hey stranger.

972
00:53:29,250 --> 00:53:30,640
Hey.

973
00:53:30,640 --> 00:53:31,740
You working tonight?

974
00:53:34,070 --> 00:53:36,728
No, I'm just looking for Trevor.

975
00:53:36,728 --> 00:53:37,800
He's around

976
00:53:37,800 --> 00:53:39,796
I don't know where he could be.

977
00:53:39,796 --> 00:53:40,629
So.

978
00:53:41,910 --> 00:53:43,303
How are your kids?

979
00:53:44,450 --> 00:53:45,283
Fine.

980
00:53:46,520 --> 00:53:47,570
How's your old man?

981
00:53:51,030 --> 00:53:51,863
He died.

982
00:53:55,680 --> 00:53:57,210
That's awful.

983
00:53:57,210 --> 00:53:58,053
I'm sorry.

984
00:53:59,160 --> 00:54:01,510
That's gotta be really tough on your kids, huh?

985
00:54:03,534 --> 00:54:04,367
Oh.

986
00:54:06,030 --> 00:54:07,420
I thought you were talking about my father,

987
00:54:07,420 --> 00:54:12,170
no, no my boyfriend, he's still alive.

988
00:54:12,170 --> 00:54:13,370
He's watching the girls.

989
00:54:14,890 --> 00:54:16,290
Any more at home like him?

990
00:54:17,730 --> 00:54:19,190
Hey, precious.

991
00:54:19,190 --> 00:54:21,323
You wanna go again?

992
00:54:22,690 --> 00:54:23,623
She's with me.

993
00:54:25,160 --> 00:54:25,993
Oh.

994
00:54:28,471 --> 00:54:29,304
Oh, I get it.

995
00:54:31,810 --> 00:54:32,643
Good.

996
00:54:33,930 --> 00:54:36,023
Good, now go on, take it somewhere else.

997
00:54:39,550 --> 00:54:42,343
Um, gotta get ready for my set.

998
00:54:46,060 --> 00:54:48,673
Do you maybe wanna go get some dinner later?

999
00:54:49,722 --> 00:54:51,687
Oh, yeah, maybe.

1000
00:54:53,821 --> 00:54:55,473
I don't know if I'll have time.

1001
00:54:59,980 --> 00:55:00,813
Bye.

1002
00:55:02,253 --> 00:55:03,503
Hey precious.

1003
00:55:04,773 --> 00:55:06,593
Can um, can I watch?

1004
00:55:08,730 --> 00:55:10,100
Watch what?

1005
00:55:10,100 --> 00:55:12,030
You and your friend.

1006
00:55:12,030 --> 00:55:13,223
Hey Ginger.

1007
00:55:15,700 --> 00:55:16,970
Hello Mr. Trevor.

1008
00:55:16,970 --> 00:55:17,803
What, are you stoned?

1009
00:55:17,803 --> 00:55:19,240
Hey, I've got money.

1010
00:55:19,240 --> 00:55:20,290
Excuse me a second.

1011
00:55:22,380 --> 00:55:23,230
Hold up, come on.

1012
00:55:26,970 --> 00:55:28,570
So you got it?

1013
00:55:28,570 --> 00:55:29,512
Got what?

1014
00:55:29,512 --> 00:55:30,460
My product.

1015
00:55:30,460 --> 00:55:31,293
Oh.

1016
00:55:32,460 --> 00:55:33,293
It's safe.

1017
00:55:34,844 --> 00:55:35,933
Wait a minute, hey,

1018
00:55:35,933 --> 00:55:36,766
what the hell does that mean?

1019
00:55:36,766 --> 00:55:37,599
Don't you get it?

1020
00:55:37,599 --> 00:55:38,432
She doesn't wanna talk to you.

1021
00:55:38,432 --> 00:55:39,570
Look, just stay out of this.

1022
00:55:39,570 --> 00:55:40,880
No you stay out of this.

1023
00:55:40,880 --> 00:55:42,546
Hey, stop it.
Whoa, whoa, whoa.

1024
00:55:42,546 --> 00:55:44,519
Settle down boys.
Stop, stop fighting!

1025
00:55:44,519 --> 00:55:49,186
(loud punching)
No, don't hurt that man!

1026
00:55:50,249 --> 00:55:51,082
Ow!

1027
00:55:54,058 --> 00:55:54,990
Where the hell is it?

1028
00:55:54,990 --> 00:55:56,044
Where's my money.

1029
00:55:56,044 --> 00:55:57,081
(Trevor breathing heavily)

1030
00:55:57,081 --> 00:55:58,870
All right, look.

1031
00:55:58,870 --> 00:56:01,363
Just give me whatever you've got-

1032
00:56:03,750 --> 00:56:04,883
Good Ginger, you crazy bitch.

1033
00:56:06,323 --> 00:56:10,704
We're out of here.

1034
00:56:10,704 --> 00:56:13,454
(loud bar music)

1035
00:56:20,470 --> 00:56:22,383
Hey, come back.

1036
00:56:23,530 --> 00:56:24,370
You don't wanna mess with me,

1037
00:56:24,370 --> 00:56:25,203
take my word for that.

1038
00:56:25,203 --> 00:56:27,156
But, I love you.

1039
00:56:27,156 --> 00:56:31,157
(loud kick)
(man groans in pain)

1040
00:56:31,157 --> 00:56:34,074
(tires screeching)

1041
00:56:42,938 --> 00:56:45,771
(loud rock music)

1042
00:57:30,089 --> 00:57:33,089
(car door slamming)

1043
00:57:41,605 --> 00:57:42,563
(phone ringing)
Suzy?

1044
00:57:42,563 --> 00:57:43,396
D.J.

1045
00:57:43,396 --> 00:57:45,164
Where's Suzy, I wanna talk to Suzy.

1046
00:57:45,164 --> 00:57:46,190
I have too much to deal with right now.

1047
00:57:46,190 --> 00:57:47,023
Hello.

1048
00:57:47,023 --> 00:57:48,880
Sean, I think we gotta call the police.

1049
00:57:48,880 --> 00:57:50,920
This isn't Sean, it's D.J.

1050
00:57:50,920 --> 00:57:52,310
Oh, I must've dialed the wrong number,

1051
00:57:52,310 --> 00:57:53,430
I'm terribly sorry.

1052
00:57:53,430 --> 00:57:54,803
Suzy, where were you tonight?

1053
00:57:54,803 --> 00:57:55,673
I had to lie to your mom,

1054
00:57:55,673 --> 00:57:56,850
I had to lie to the kids.

1055
00:57:56,850 --> 00:57:58,184
Yeah, it hurts doesn't it?

1056
00:57:58,184 --> 00:57:59,260
Just don't make me lie to you.

1057
00:57:59,260 --> 00:58:00,093
I wanna talk to the woman I married.

1058
00:58:00,093 --> 00:58:01,020
She's not here!

1059
00:58:01,020 --> 00:58:02,712
The bitch almost got us all killed.

1060
00:58:02,712 --> 00:58:04,291
Suzy, what in the hell's going on here?

1061
00:58:04,291 --> 00:58:05,564
Are you deaf?
Suzy!

1062
00:58:05,564 --> 00:58:06,916
(door slams)

1063
00:58:06,916 --> 00:58:07,749
Suzy!

1064
00:58:07,749 --> 00:58:09,109
Hello? Hello?

1065
00:58:09,109 --> 00:58:10,310
What's going on, is somebody there?

1066
00:58:10,310 --> 00:58:11,890
Hello?

1067
00:58:11,890 --> 00:58:13,440
Yeah, I'm calling for Ginger.

1068
00:58:14,840 --> 00:58:16,440
Didn't work out, the deal's off.

1069
00:58:17,430 --> 00:58:18,263
Who's this?

1070
00:58:20,260 --> 00:58:21,543
A friend of Ginger's.

1071
00:58:24,230 --> 00:58:25,380
She's through with you.

1072
00:58:26,689 --> 00:58:28,580
You listen to me, whoever you are.

1073
00:58:28,580 --> 00:58:31,960
You tell her that I want back what belongs to me.

1074
00:58:31,960 --> 00:58:33,560
Otherwise she's gonna disappear.

1075
00:58:34,404 --> 00:58:35,904
You tell her that.

1076
00:58:36,770 --> 00:58:38,000
Hello?

1077
00:58:38,000 --> 00:58:38,904
You understand that?

1078
00:58:38,904 --> 00:58:40,956
Hello? Hello?
Suzy.

1079
00:58:40,956 --> 00:58:42,158
Who the hell's Suzy?
Suzy.

1080
00:58:42,158 --> 00:58:45,158
What's goin on here?
Suzy

1081
00:58:47,012 --> 00:58:49,679
(phone dialing)

1082
00:58:51,060 --> 00:58:52,866
Hey Martha, I don't know what's going on.

1083
00:58:52,866 --> 00:58:54,327
I need you to watch the girls.

1084
00:58:54,327 --> 00:58:57,244
(tires screeching)

1085
00:59:00,033 --> 00:59:03,283
(dramatic music plays)

1086
00:59:05,982 --> 00:59:06,815
Hey hun.

1087
00:59:08,671 --> 00:59:10,438
Hey, Ginger-

1088
00:59:10,438 --> 00:59:13,021
(dogs barking)

1089
00:59:18,109 --> 00:59:20,526
(door slams)

1090
00:59:34,932 --> 00:59:36,044
(Suzy knocking on door)

1091
00:59:36,044 --> 00:59:37,432
Hello?

1092
00:59:37,432 --> 00:59:38,432
Dr. Scanlon?

1093
00:59:39,390 --> 00:59:40,223
Eric.

1094
00:59:41,200 --> 00:59:42,033
Dr. Scanlon.

1095
00:59:43,268 --> 00:59:44,101
Hello?

1096
00:59:45,180 --> 00:59:46,590
Suzy?

1097
00:59:46,590 --> 00:59:48,580
Don't you move, don't you move.

1098
00:59:48,580 --> 00:59:49,413
You stay there.

1099
00:59:52,330 --> 00:59:53,163
Sit down Eric.

1100
00:59:53,163 --> 00:59:53,996
Okay.

1101
00:59:57,040 --> 00:59:59,163
We haven't met, I'm Ginger.

1102
01:00:00,630 --> 01:00:02,257
What's going on?

1103
01:00:02,257 --> 01:00:03,680
Nothing much,

1104
01:00:03,680 --> 01:00:05,853
just took us a little trip to San Diego.

1105
01:00:07,380 --> 01:00:08,580
Any particular reason?

1106
01:00:09,670 --> 01:00:11,190
Money.

1107
01:00:11,190 --> 01:00:12,779
Well what about money?

1108
01:00:12,779 --> 01:00:14,690
Oh, I had to make some.

1109
01:00:16,368 --> 01:00:18,060
And how did you do that?

1110
01:00:18,060 --> 01:00:19,283
The old-fashioned way.

1111
01:00:20,810 --> 01:00:21,810
With a gun.

1112
01:00:23,280 --> 01:00:24,113
With this.

1113
01:00:28,120 --> 01:00:28,953
I see.

1114
01:00:30,780 --> 01:00:32,230
How long you been doing that?

1115
01:00:37,076 --> 01:00:37,909
Forever.

1116
01:00:40,943 --> 01:00:42,560
Don't you tell Suzy.

1117
01:00:42,560 --> 01:00:44,710
All that girl knows is how to fold laundry.

1118
01:00:45,660 --> 01:00:48,190
She didn't even exist before those kids.

1119
01:00:48,190 --> 01:00:51,180
We created her, not the other way around, okay?

1120
01:00:51,180 --> 01:00:52,013
Okay.

1121
01:00:53,140 --> 01:00:55,690
Just ask Suzy what she remembers before her kids.

1122
01:00:56,900 --> 01:00:58,623
Well, I know what she remembers.

1123
01:01:00,096 --> 01:01:02,837
And that's the way it's gonna stay, hm?

1124
01:01:02,837 --> 01:01:05,510
You know, I think you'd be really surprised

1125
01:01:05,510 --> 01:01:07,810
