01:14:32,031 --> 01:14:33,355
Molly.

1401
01:14:33,355 --> 01:14:36,438
(Suzy starts crying)

1402
01:14:39,216 --> 01:14:41,966
(vacuum running)

1403
01:14:47,573 --> 01:14:50,240
(ominous music)

1404
01:15:29,823 --> 01:15:32,647
(engine starting)

1405
01:15:32,647 --> 01:15:35,314
(radio playing)

1406
01:15:38,373 --> 01:15:39,373
There we go.

1407
01:15:41,775 --> 01:15:42,775
Thanks, Dad.

1408
01:15:45,080 --> 01:15:46,663
Where are we going?

1409
01:15:47,620 --> 01:15:49,973
Anywhere you'd like, sugar.

1410
01:15:49,973 --> 01:15:51,390
Don't touch me.

1411
01:15:52,269 --> 01:15:54,019
Besides this, Suzy.

1412
01:15:58,618 --> 01:16:00,285
I would like that.

1413
01:16:04,658 --> 01:16:07,825
(laughing) that's good.

1414
01:16:07,825 --> 01:16:11,325
(both speaking inaudibly)

1415
01:16:29,457 --> 01:16:32,207
(fire crackling)

1416
01:16:35,150 --> 01:16:36,840
Oh my god.

1417
01:16:36,840 --> 01:16:37,673
Daddy?

1418
01:16:39,580 --> 01:16:41,854
Daddy, help me.

1419
01:16:41,854 --> 01:16:42,687
Help me!

1420
01:16:43,863 --> 01:16:44,696
Daddy.

1421
01:16:45,626 --> 01:16:48,439
(Suzy coughing)

1422
01:16:48,439 --> 01:16:49,272
Daddy?

1423
01:17:02,664 --> 01:17:05,997
(phone buttons beeping)

1424
01:17:08,010 --> 01:17:08,843
Hello?

1425
01:17:11,590 --> 01:17:15,293
Someone tried to set us on fire.

1426
01:17:16,510 --> 01:17:17,960
Suzy?

1427
01:17:17,960 --> 01:17:18,793
Where are you?

1428
01:17:21,321 --> 01:17:22,682
Where am I?

1429
01:17:22,682 --> 01:17:24,559
I don't know.

1430
01:17:24,559 --> 01:17:25,477
Where am I?

1431
01:17:27,360 --> 01:17:29,693
(loud thud)

1432
01:17:32,216 --> 01:17:34,883
(phone ringing)

1433
01:17:38,740 --> 01:17:41,073
(dial tone)

1434
01:17:53,761 --> 01:17:56,428
(phone ringing)

1435
01:17:58,124 --> 01:17:58,957
Your daughter's here.

1436
01:17:58,957 --> 01:18:00,559
She inhaled a lot of smoke,

1437
01:18:00,559 --> 01:18:01,930
and we had to pump her stomach.

1438
01:18:01,930 --> 01:18:02,763
Where is she?

1439
01:18:02,763 --> 01:18:04,370
I think we should let her rest right now.

1440
01:18:04,370 --> 01:18:05,960
She's my daughter damn it.

1441
01:18:05,960 --> 01:18:07,830
I have to see her.

1442
01:18:07,830 --> 01:18:09,553
I think she tried to kill herself.

1443
01:18:15,512 --> 01:18:16,570
(car door slams)

1444
01:18:16,570 --> 01:18:17,920
Okay guys, we're going home.

1445
01:18:17,920 --> 01:18:19,840
Did you find Mommy?

1446
01:18:19,840 --> 01:18:21,007
Soon.

1447
01:18:34,887 --> 01:18:36,304
She's not here.

1448
01:18:38,670 --> 01:18:41,980
Yeah, Dr. Scanlon? This is Sean Mitchell.

1449
01:18:41,980 --> 01:18:43,433
Have you heard from Suzy?

1450
01:18:44,650 --> 01:18:47,183
I can't find her and she's not at her mother's.

1451
01:18:49,304 --> 01:18:51,554
I think I scared her, she told me some stuff.

1452
01:18:53,420 --> 01:18:55,820
I left her home alone in the house.

1453
01:18:55,820 --> 01:18:59,083
Could you call me as soon as you get this message?

1454
01:18:59,083 --> 01:19:02,659
Thank you.

1455
01:19:02,659 --> 01:19:03,492
Molly.

1456
01:19:04,419 --> 01:19:05,350
Rosie.

1457
01:19:05,350 --> 01:19:06,683
Suzy, thank god.

1458
01:19:07,570 --> 01:19:10,480
Oh, where's Sean?

1459
01:19:10,480 --> 01:19:13,510
He's okay. The kids too.

1460
01:19:13,510 --> 01:19:15,136
You'll be fine darling.

1461
01:19:15,136 --> 01:19:15,969
No.

1462
01:19:15,969 --> 01:19:16,809
Won't you be fine?

1463
01:19:22,250 --> 01:19:23,083
Suzy?

1464
01:19:26,880 --> 01:19:27,713
Suzy?

1465
01:19:31,040 --> 01:19:31,873
Suzy?

1466
01:19:37,349 --> 01:19:38,182
Sean.

1467
01:19:41,420 --> 01:19:42,253
Suzy.

1468
01:19:45,780 --> 01:19:48,333
Okay, doctor says you can go home.

1469
01:19:49,610 --> 01:19:50,640
Where's Sean?

1470
01:19:50,640 --> 01:19:51,809
Did he call?

1471
01:19:51,809 --> 01:19:53,390
No, not yet.

1472
01:19:53,390 --> 01:19:54,700
Let's get you dressed.

1473
01:19:54,700 --> 01:19:55,532
But what about Eric?

1474
01:19:55,532 --> 01:19:57,150
I think I should talk to Eric.

1475
01:19:57,150 --> 01:19:58,010
You will.

1476
01:19:58,010 --> 01:19:59,830
Oh come on honey, let's go home.

1477
01:19:59,830 --> 01:20:01,480
He's given up on me, hasn't he?

1478
01:20:01,480 --> 01:20:03,881
No, no one's given up on you.

1479
01:20:03,881 --> 01:20:05,840
But it worries me to hear you think that, honey.

1480
01:20:05,840 --> 01:20:07,073
Come on now, let's go.

1481
01:20:07,073 --> 01:20:08,073
Why?

1482
01:20:08,073 --> 01:20:09,780
Because sweetheart,

1483
01:20:09,780 --> 01:20:11,447
what happened the other night was terrible.

1484
01:20:11,447 --> 01:20:14,280
And we're just trying to figure out why.

1485
01:20:14,280 --> 01:20:15,180
It was terrible.

1486
01:20:16,280 --> 01:20:19,100
I told Sean terrible things, I'm horrible.

1487
01:20:19,100 --> 01:20:20,760
Darling, that's not true.

1488
01:20:20,760 --> 01:20:22,480
It is true!

1489
01:20:22,480 --> 01:20:23,980
There are others worse than me.

1490
01:20:23,980 --> 01:20:25,770
What are you talking about?

1491
01:20:25,770 --> 01:20:28,214
D.J. and Ginger,

1492
01:20:28,214 --> 01:20:29,664
and others I don't even know.

1493
01:20:30,625 --> 01:20:32,303
Oh god, I can feel them.

1494
01:20:32,303 --> 01:20:33,603
I can feel them coming up.

1495
01:20:36,140 --> 01:20:38,640
(Suzy crying)

1496
01:20:40,440 --> 01:20:42,133
I don't know what else to do.

1497
01:20:43,030 --> 01:20:44,540
I've called Martha,

1498
01:20:44,540 --> 01:20:47,210
and I've left messages for her uncle.

1499
01:20:47,210 --> 01:20:48,043
Yeah.

1500
01:20:49,890 --> 01:20:50,723
Of course.

1501
01:20:52,809 --> 01:20:54,059
All right, I'll call you.

1502
01:20:54,960 --> 01:20:55,993
Thanks Dr. Scanlon.

1503
01:20:59,280 --> 01:21:00,662
Daddy?

1504
01:21:00,662 --> 01:21:01,495
Is Mommy dead?

1505
01:21:03,530 --> 01:21:05,238
No baby, no, no.

1506
01:21:05,238 --> 01:21:08,088
(Rosie crying)

1507
01:21:08,088 --> 01:21:11,171
(door creaking open)

1508
01:21:15,800 --> 01:21:18,023
Go lie down and I'll make you a cup of tea.

1509
01:21:41,362 --> 01:21:44,779
(rapid knocking at door)

1510
01:21:46,100 --> 01:21:46,933
Oh god.

1511
01:21:46,933 --> 01:21:48,660
She's gonna be all right, Sean.

1512
01:21:48,660 --> 01:21:49,493
What happened? Where is she?

1513
01:21:49,493 --> 01:21:52,270
She's at her mother's, she's resting.

1514
01:21:52,270 --> 01:21:53,980
She set her car on fire.

1515
01:21:53,980 --> 01:21:56,901
But she's gonna be fine Sean.

1516
01:21:56,901 --> 01:21:57,734
Oh my god.

1517
01:21:57,734 --> 01:21:58,740
Molly!

1518
01:21:58,740 --> 01:21:59,710
Rosie!

1519
01:21:59,710 --> 01:22:00,543
Sean, wait, wait.

1520
01:22:00,543 --> 01:22:01,557
For what? I gotta see her.

1521
01:22:01,557 --> 01:22:03,300
No, no, not yet.

1522
01:22:03,300 --> 01:22:06,000
Why? She doesn't wanna see me?

1523
01:22:06,000 --> 01:22:07,320
Eventually, yes, of course.

1524
01:22:07,320 --> 01:22:11,690
But right now she's still a little shaky.

1525
01:22:11,690 --> 01:22:12,523
I know.

1526
01:22:13,400 --> 01:22:14,233
I went nuts.

1527
01:22:15,776 --> 01:22:18,350
I was afraid for the girls, I was...

1528
01:22:18,350 --> 01:22:19,754
I should never have left her alone.

1529
01:22:19,754 --> 01:22:21,279
Sean, no Sean. It wasn't your fault.

1530
01:22:21,279 --> 01:22:22,112
Yes it is.

1531
01:22:22,112 --> 01:22:23,749
Is that what that doctor's been telling you?

1532
01:22:23,749 --> 01:22:25,020
No!

1533
01:22:25,020 --> 01:22:26,170
I've gotta call him.

1534
01:22:26,170 --> 01:22:27,003
No, no, Sean.

1535
01:22:27,003 --> 01:22:28,130
I don't think she'd want you to do that.

1536
01:22:28,130 --> 01:22:28,963
You know,

1537
01:22:30,600 --> 01:22:32,800
she's been having second thoughts about him.

1538
01:22:34,763 --> 01:22:35,803
We all have.

1539
01:22:37,059 --> 01:22:37,893
Why?

1540
01:22:39,000 --> 01:22:40,640
Because of what happened last night.

1541
01:22:40,640 --> 01:22:42,100
It wasn't Eric's fault, it was me.

1542
01:22:42,100 --> 01:22:43,073
I went crazy.

1543
01:22:45,090 --> 01:22:46,240
Why did you go crazy?

1544
01:22:49,390 --> 01:22:50,782
She told me some things.

1545
01:22:52,850 --> 01:22:53,837
She told you?

1546
01:22:55,432 --> 01:22:58,630
Or did one of the personalities?

1547
01:22:58,630 --> 01:23:01,740
D.J. Ginger, Victoria, Bonnie?

1548
01:23:01,740 --> 01:23:03,640
How can we be sure any of it was true?

1549
01:23:05,630 --> 01:23:06,830
You don't think it is?

1550
01:23:09,430 --> 01:23:10,282
I'm not sure.

1551
01:23:12,340 --> 01:23:13,450
Well what about Molly and Rosie?

1552
01:23:13,450 --> 01:23:14,990
They should see her.

1553
01:23:14,990 --> 01:23:17,123
That's her biggest worry too, Sean.

1554
01:23:20,200 --> 01:23:22,610
Right now she's afraid

1555
01:23:23,809 --> 01:23:25,960
for the children to see her the way she is.

1556
01:23:29,690 --> 01:23:31,510
Remember the first time I made this?

1557
01:23:31,510 --> 01:23:32,343
Mm hmm.

1558
01:23:33,180 --> 01:23:35,117
You dropped half of it on your dress?

1559
01:23:35,117 --> 01:23:36,870
(Suzy laughs)

1560
01:23:36,870 --> 01:23:39,236
What size piece you want, big or little?

1561
01:23:39,236 --> 01:23:40,068
Big.

1562
01:23:48,663 --> 01:23:51,023
I'll be right back Suzy, you wait right here.

1563
01:24:03,059 --> 01:24:04,300
What are you doing here?

1564
01:24:04,300 --> 01:24:05,133
Didn't Chester talk to you?

1565
01:24:05,133 --> 01:24:07,163
We need to see her.
Hi girls.

1566
01:24:26,841 --> 01:24:30,591
(group talking and laughing)

1567
01:24:45,374 --> 01:24:46,590
You get everything you wanted there?

1568
01:24:46,590 --> 01:24:48,003
I'm good with the drinks.

1569
01:24:48,003 --> 01:24:49,651
You're doing okay there, aren't you?

1570
01:24:49,651 --> 01:24:51,330
All right, good news.

1571
01:24:51,330 --> 01:24:52,930
You boys okay?

1572
01:24:52,930 --> 01:24:54,430
Yeah, bring her out.

1573
01:24:56,250 --> 01:24:58,340
Where are you sweetie?

1574
01:24:58,340 --> 01:24:59,173
Suzy?

1575
01:24:59,173 --> 01:25:00,006
Hey come on out now.

1576
01:25:01,916 --> 01:25:03,610
Come on out and play Suzy.

1577
01:25:03,610 --> 01:25:04,790
Hold on for now.

1578
01:25:04,790 --> 01:25:06,460
Now don't you wanna come out and play?

1579
01:25:06,460 --> 01:25:07,780
Suzy, where are you?

1580
01:25:07,780 --> 01:25:08,970
Now don't you wanna dance for our friends?

1581
01:25:08,970 --> 01:25:10,333
Now come on out.
Yeah!

1582
01:25:11,396 --> 01:25:14,148
Come on out Suzy.

1583
01:25:14,148 --> 01:25:15,898
Come on Suzy.

1584
01:25:16,859 --> 01:25:18,780
Suzy, where are you?

1585
01:25:18,780 --> 01:25:20,890
I'm sorry Sean, please not yet.

1586
01:25:20,890 --> 01:25:22,450
We're looking for another doctor.

1587
01:25:22,450 --> 01:25:24,850
Just give this some time, it'll work itself out.

1588
01:25:26,280 --> 01:25:27,983
Rosie, sweetheart.

1589
01:25:27,983 --> 01:25:30,337
Wait a minute!
Mommy!

1590
01:25:30,337 --> 01:25:31,170
Mommy!

1591
01:25:34,037 --> 01:25:35,427
Mommy?

1592
01:25:35,427 --> 01:25:36,727
Mommy!

1593
01:25:36,727 --> 01:25:38,071
Mommy!

1594
01:25:38,071 --> 01:25:39,213
Mommy!
Come on, Martha.

1595
01:25:39,213 --> 01:25:41,010
Wait a sec, just let her go.

1596
01:25:41,010 --> 01:25:43,327
Martha, it's all right, let her go.

1597
01:25:46,630 --> 01:25:47,720
Rosie?

1598
01:25:47,720 --> 01:25:49,309
Rosie where are you?
Mommy?

1599
01:25:49,309 --> 01:25:51,400
Mommy don't, don't Mommy.

1600
01:25:51,400 --> 01:25:52,461
Mommy!

1601
01:25:52,461 --> 01:25:53,336
Mommy?

1602
01:25:53,336 --> 01:25:55,126
Suzy, oh my god.

1603
01:25:55,126 --> 01:25:55,959
Rosie come here.

1604
01:25:55,959 --> 01:25:57,861
Mommy? Mommy!

1605
01:25:57,861 --> 01:25:59,222
Get your hands off of her!

1606
01:25:59,222 --> 01:26:00,479
No, let go!

1607
01:26:00,479 --> 01:26:03,786
(Rosie shouting)

1608
01:26:03,786 --> 01:26:05,396
Suzy-

1609
01:26:05,396 --> 01:26:06,780
Suzy.

1610
01:26:06,780 --> 01:26:07,989
Suzy!

1611
01:26:07,989 --> 01:26:09,637
Suzy!

1612
01:26:09,637 --> 01:26:10,473
Honey?

1613
01:26:10,473 --> 01:26:11,957
Now do you understand?

1614
01:26:11,957 --> 01:26:13,007
Honey.

1615
01:26:13,007 --> 01:26:14,677
(loud knocking on door)

1616
01:26:14,677 --> 01:26:18,393
Honey, I'm gonna call Dr. Scanlon, okay?

1617
01:26:19,420 --> 01:26:21,010
Sean, wait a minute.

1618
01:26:21,010 --> 01:26:22,490
Wait a minute, I don't think you should call.

1619
01:26:22,490 --> 01:26:23,880
Well I'm calling him.

1620
01:26:23,880 --> 01:26:25,483
Stop, this is my house damn it.

1621
01:26:25,483 --> 01:26:26,316
What are you hiding?

1622
01:26:26,316 --> 01:26:27,234
What are you trying to make her forget?

1623
01:26:27,234 --> 01:26:28,067
I'm not trying to hide anything,

1624
01:26:28,067 --> 01:26:29,013
Keeping her away from her family.

1625
01:26:29,013 --> 01:26:29,846
She's my daughter for God's sake,

1626
01:26:29,846 --> 01:26:30,679
I'm trying to protect her.

1627
01:26:30,679 --> 01:26:31,512
Hello, may I speak to Dr. Scanlon please?

1628
01:26:31,512 --> 01:26:32,890
What about your daughters?

1629
01:26:32,890 --> 01:26:34,237
Dragging them out here, making them-

1630
01:26:34,237 --> 01:26:35,210
What could be worse for our daughters

1631
01:26:35,210 --> 01:26:36,360
than Suzy going crazy?

1632
01:26:36,360 --> 01:26:38,240
Suzy killing herself.

1633
01:26:38,240 --> 01:26:39,076
That would be worse.

1634
01:26:39,076 --> 01:26:41,493
(loud crash)

1635
01:26:44,100 --> 01:26:45,350
I'm not gonna hurt you.

1636
01:26:48,308 --> 01:26:49,141
I know.

1637
01:26:50,630 --> 01:26:51,463
Good.

1638
01:26:54,200 --> 01:26:55,630
That's good.

1639
01:26:55,630 --> 01:26:57,380
Oh, I knew you'd say that.

1640
01:26:58,680 --> 01:26:59,543
You did? Why?

1641
01:27:01,243 --> 01:27:04,193
I won over those men.

1642
01:27:09,550 --> 01:27:10,823
Now you're next.

1643
01:27:11,930 --> 01:27:12,763
Suzy I-

1644
01:27:12,763 --> 01:27:14,173
And I will die first.

1645
01:27:17,480 --> 01:27:19,120
That's what you want.

1646
01:27:19,120 --> 01:27:20,320
Why would I want that?

1647
01:27:22,397 --> 01:27:23,814
Because.

1648
01:27:27,610 --> 01:27:30,190
You think I'm your dad, don't you?

1649
01:27:30,190 --> 01:27:31,340
Messing with your head.

1650
01:27:33,470 --> 01:27:34,303
Well he's dead.

1651
01:27:35,770 --> 01:27:37,270
And he can't hurt you anymore.

1652
01:27:39,570 --> 01:27:40,853
Can I talk to Suzy now?

1653
01:27:45,360 --> 01:27:46,193
Sure.

1654
01:27:48,620 --> 01:27:50,020
That means no, doesn't it?

1655
01:27:52,070 --> 01:27:54,452
You're somebody new, somebody deeper.

1656
01:27:56,382 --> 01:27:58,050
(Suzy laughs)

1657
01:27:58,050 --> 01:27:58,883
Suzy?

1658
01:28:02,340 --> 01:28:04,173
Victoria? Bonnie?

1659
01:28:05,010 --> 01:28:06,860
Can any of you hear me?

1660
01:28:06,860 --> 01:28:08,303
If you can, listen.

1661
01:28:09,140 --> 01:28:11,540
I'm here talking to somebody who wants you dead.

1662
01:28:12,570 --> 01:28:14,823
She thinks everything's your fault.

1663
01:28:16,110 --> 01:28:18,160
She thinks you deserve to die,

1664
01:28:18,160 --> 01:28:19,809
that that would solve everything.

1665
01:28:23,523 --> 01:28:25,441
They're already dead.

1666
01:28:29,032 --> 01:28:31,950
And you know why she thinks that?

1667
01:28:33,380 --> 01:28:34,480
Because then at least,

1668
01:28:37,400 --> 01:28:39,367
there would be some sense in the world.

1669
01:28:41,880 --> 01:28:45,193
I'm bad because I hurt so much.

1670
01:28:47,010 --> 01:28:48,110
That's what you think.

1671
01:28:49,798 --> 01:28:51,013
But you're not bad.

1672
01:28:53,210 --> 01:28:55,843
Something happened to you when you were little.

1673
01:28:58,120 --> 01:28:59,403
And you were helpless.

1674
01:29:01,809 --> 01:29:02,643
Not bad.

1675
01:29:04,420 --> 01:29:05,393
Helpless.

1676
01:29:09,140 --> 01:29:11,223
Let me talk to Suzy.

1677
01:29:16,050 --> 01:29:16,993
